msg: The user should be notified of non working features he uses, preferably by a hard fail. So silently removing the default value is a bad idea.

author: tfischer
msg: Remove default values CURRENT_DATE, CURRENT_TIME and CURRENT_TIMESTAMP in SQL generation
if these functions are not supported for the database the SQL is generated for (which is the case for MSSQL and MYSQL)
This enables the test project to be run for these databases without the onSqlError=continue option
